The paper deals with approximation algorithms for constraint satisfaction problems, which are central to computer science and fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of Pareto optimization and multiobjective optimization also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms and the design of data structures, which are topics in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with combinatorial optimization, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
